    {
      "id": "5038a5fd_69941426",
      "file_path": "datafile-app-server/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/collectors/datafile/http/DfcHttpClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 65,
      "message": "Is there a benefit to using CountDownLatch instead of using: client.get().response().block() ?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "remigiusz.janeczek@nokia.com",
        "username": "rjanecze"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-17 21:04:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "03b8a3b0_2c9664a2",
      "file_path": "datafile-app-server/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/collectors/datafile/http/DfcHttpClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "Why pass those values in such a way? For me it's hard to understand what's happening.\n\nI would propose solution in lines of:\n\n client.get().response((responseReceiver, byteBufFlux) -> {\n     response = byteBufFlux.aggregate().asInputStream();\n     if(isResponseOk(responseReceiver)){\n         return saveFile(response);\n     } else {\n         retrun Mono.error( createException(response) )\n     }\n }).then().block();\n\n\nfrom the response() lambda you should probably create RuntimeExceptions with correct message/stacktrace, and the whole client.get().response()... could be wrapped by try catch and then DatafileTaskException could be created.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "remigiusz.janeczek@nokia.com",
        "username": "rjanecze"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-17 21:04:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "58f8f449_b827a4c7",
      "file_path": "datafile-app-server/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/collectors/datafile/http/DfcHttpClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 147,
      "message": "You could just do:\n\n int port = fileServerData.port().isPresent() ? fileserverData.port().get() : HttpUtils.HTTP_DEFAULT_PORT;\n return \"http://\" + fileServerData.serverAddress() + \":\" + port + remoteFile;\n\nor:\n\n return fileServerData.port().orElse(HttpUtils.HTTP_DEFAULT_PORT)\n     .map(port -> \"http://\" + fileServerData.serverAddress() + \":\" + HttpUtils.HTTP_DEFAULT_PORT + remoteFile)\n     .get();",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "remigiusz.janeczek@nokia.com",
        "username": "rjanecze"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-17 21:04:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
