      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 65,
      "message": "Actually, Yes 😊, I agree with you with block() and initially it was in my plans. But now DFC was written in such way, I was unable to use it (please, see small part of my earlier logs):\n\n\"\njava.lang.IllegalStateException: block()/blockFirst()/blockLast() are blocking, which is not supported in thread FileCollectorWorker-2\n\tat reactor.core.publisher.BlockingSingleSubscriber.blockingGet(BlockingSingleSubscriber.java:83)\n\tat reactor.core.publisher.Mono.block(Mono.java:1679)\n\tat org.onap.dcaegen2.collectors.datafile.http.DfcHttpClient.collectFile(DfcHttpClient.java:82)\n\"\n\nThat was the reason of using subscribe() and CountDownLatch.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6675,
        "name": "Krzysztof Gajewski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "krzysztof.gajewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "gajos"
      },
      "updated": "2020-12-18 22:45:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5038a5fd_69941426",
